name: change -- party composition
description: change of coalition party composition

name: election -- regular
description: election at the end of a legislative period

name: Special issue
description: single issue parties focussing on particular topics only

name: election -- dissolution
description: dissolution of parliament and elections before the end of the official term

name: losing confidence vote -- RECODE
description: cabinet fails by loosing e.g. vote of confidence, investiture vote, constructive vote of no-confidence

name: Populist
description: populist party

name: splinter group
description: New party is formed as splinter group of another party.

name: division
description: One party divides into two or more new parties.

name: merger
description: New party is formed by merging two or more parties that cede to exist.

name: joining larger group
description: Party joins a larger group without forming a new party.

name: successor
description: Successor party formed by former activists of the predecessor party that ceased to exist.

name: single politician
description: formed by single (prominent) politician

name: no seat
description: Largest party that won no seats in an election and less than one percent vote share.

name: Transition
description: social movement that took part in an election in the process of democratic transition

name: District
description: party or group in special district provided by national election law

name: electoral law minority
description: Party that benefits from electoral law for minority parties.

name: other (family)
description: group of others that belongs to a party family

name: one seat
description: Parties that won one seat in a single election and less than one percent vote share.

name: no party
description: used for entries that are no parties and were this proporty does not follow from the party family classification ('no family')

name: Millionaire
description: party created by business person with significant private funding

name: snippets
description: ParlGov snippets on Github -- https://github.com/hdigital/parlgov-snippets

name: minister and parliamentary group
description: minister and member of cabinet parliamentary group

name: Arab lists
description: Arab satellite lists (Israel only)

name: Financial
description: financial topics of single issue parties
